response.original_title: Our Best-Kept Secret: Celebrating The Rich Heritage Of The Township of Rideau Lakes
response.overview: The LACAC of the Township of Rideau Lakes is charged with the happy duty of identifying local structures of heritage significance promoting and sharing our researches and encouraging the preservation of buildings that reflect our rich tradition and experience. But heritage is more than picturesque structures of stone and wood. Our greatest treasure of heritage are our people whose lives, work and play, studies and worship find home along the lakes and hills, farms and communities of Rideau Country. Let us share with you a few minutes of our lifetimes, a few memories of our heritage, a few scenes of our paradise.
response.title: Our Best-Kept Secret: Celebrating The Rich Heritage Of The Township of Rideau Lakes
